The paper discusses a Question Paraphrase Retrieval (QPR) system, which is a subfield of Information Retrieval (IR) and Natural Language Processing (NLP). The system is implemented using a Neural Information Retrieval (NIR) system, which falls under the category of Machine Learning (ML) and Artificial Intelligence (AI). The paper also discusses the use of a neural network sentence encoder, which is a common technique in Computational Linguistics (CL). Additionally, the paper mentions the use of a k-Nearest Neighbour index, which is a common technique in both IR and ML. Finally, the paper discusses the creation of an annotated dataset, which is a common task in Computer Vision (CV). Based on these factors, the most likely categories are cs.IR, cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, and cs.CV.
